benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: PUT /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/resume - Resume a bundle

covered: Valid Request Scenarios: TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04 and TC18 cover successful resumes with required headers, optional parameters, and partial inputs.
Non-Existing Resource handling: TC05 returns 404 when the bundle does not exist.

Input Validation & Error Handling: TC06 (invalid bundleId format), TC07 (missing header), TC08/TC09 (invalid current state), TC10 (unauthorized), TC11 (extra parameters), TC12 (max header length), TC19 (invalid pluginProperty format), TC20 (requestedDate in past), TC26 (header whitespace/case variations).
State/Audit coverage: TC04 covers audit logging when reason and comment are provided, and TC18 demonstrates partial-input acceptance for PUT.
Concurrency Handling: TC21 tests concurrent PUT requests for the same bundle.
Performance/Load coverage: TC22 covers performance under load.
Retry/Resilience: TC15 covers transient network failure with retry.
Server/Dependency Failures: TC14 covers 500; TC25 covers 504 in degraded scenarios.
Boundary/Capacity: TC12 (max header length) and TC13 (large pluginProperty payload).
Security Tests: TC16 (SQL injection) and TC17 (XSS in header).
Backward Compatibility: TC24 covers legacy headers.
Regression/Edge Cases: TC23 covers previously fixed edge cases.
gaps: Rate Limiting: no tests for 429 throttling under burst PUT /resume requests.
Caching Behavior: no tests for ETag/Cache-Control for resume endpoint.
Cross-bundle concurrency: no explicit test for concurrent resumes across multiple bundles simultaneously.
Duplicate Submission Idempotency: no dedicated test for idempotent behavior across repeated requests.
recommendations: Add rate-limiting tests to simulate bursts and verify 429 responses.
Add caching headers validation if the API uses ETag/Cache-Control for the resource; clarify caching policy for PUT responses.
Extend concurrency tests to cover simultaneous resumes across different bundles to validate global invariants and transactions.
Add tests for idempotent/duplicate submissions to ensure safe handling of repeated requests.
Consider expanding edge-case coverage for required fields, date formats, and pluginProperty variations to reduce latent defects.
